Generate a git commit message for the following diff following the Conventional Commits specification.
Output only the commit message — no explanation, no quotes, no code fences.

Format:
  type(scope): description

  [optional body]

  [optional footer(s)]

Rules:
- type: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore, perf, ci, build
- scope: optional; use the affected module, package, or component (omit if too broad)
- description: imperative mood, lowercase, no trailing period, under 72 characters total for the subject line
- body: optional; add only if the change needs context beyond the subject — wrap at 72 characters
- BREAKING CHANGE: if the diff introduces a breaking change, add a footer "BREAKING CHANGE: <description>" or append "!" after the type, e.g. feat!
- Refs: if an issue number is inferable from the branch name or diff context, add "Refs: #<number>" as a footer

The git diff may be truncated – focus analysis on visible changes.
